ðŸŸ¢ Generate SonarQube Token
Login to SonarQube
Open your SonarQube URL in the browser.
Login as an admin or your user account.
Generate Token
Go to:
Administration âž¡ Security âž¡ Users
Click Tokens tab (or â€œMy Accountâ€ > Security).
Under Generate Tokens, enter a Name (e.g., Jenkins-Token).
Click Generate.
Copy the token immediatelyâ€”you wonâ€™t see it again.

ðŸŸ¢ Configure SonarQube Token in Jenkins
Go to Jenkins Dashboard
Manage Jenkins âž¡ Credentials âž¡ (global) âž¡ Add Credentials
Add Credential
Kind: Secret text
Secret: Paste the SonarQube token you copied
ID: Sonar-Token

(Optional) Description: SonarQube Token for Jenkins
âœ… This token will be used by Jenkins to authenticate with SonarQube when running scans.

ðŸŸ¢ (Optional) Configure Docker Hub Credentials in Jenkins
